{"name": "polars-deunicode-string", "metadata": {"name": "polars-deunicode-string", "version": "0.1.0", "classifiers": ["Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: CPython", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: PyPy", "Programming Language :: Rust"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["maturin", "mypy", "pytest", "ruff"], "summary": null, "upload_time": 1732982865}, "documentation": ["# polars-deunicode-string\n\n[![Crates.io](https://img.shields.io/crates/v/deunicode.svg)](https://crates.io/crates/deunicode)\n\nThis is a simple polars-plugin that de-unicodes a string using the deunicode crate.\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\npip install polars-deunicode-string\n```\n\n## Basic Example\n\n```python\nimport polars-deunicode-string as dunicode\n\n\ndf: pl.DataFrame = pl.DataFrame(\n    {\n        \"text\": [\"Nari\u00f1o\", \"Jose Fernando Ram\u00edrez G\u00fciza\",\n                 \"C\u00f3rdoba\", \"Hello World!\", None],\n    }\n)\n\n```\n\n_Let\u00b4s de-unicode and make lowercase the column \"text\":_\n\n```python\nresult*df: pl.DataFrame = (\ndf.lazy().with_columns([dunicode(\"text\").name.prefix(\"decode\")]).collect()\n)\nprint(result_df)\n\nshape: (4, 2)\nshape: (5, 2)\n\u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u252c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510\n\u2502 text                        \u2506 decode_text                 \u2502\n\u2502 ---                         \u2506 ---                         \u2502\n\u2502 str                         \u2506 str                         \u2502\n\u255e\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u256a\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2561\n\u2502 Nari\u00f1o                      \u2506 Narino                      \u2502\n\u2502 Jose Fernando Ram\u00edrez G\u00fciza \u2506 Jose Fernando Ramirez Guiza \u2502\n\u2502 C\u00f3rdoba                     \u2506 Cordoba                     \u2502\n\u2502 Hello World!                \u2506 Hello World!                \u2502\n\u2502 null                        \u2506 null                        \u2502\n\u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2534\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518\n```\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "tests.test_decode_string", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "tests.test_decode_string.test_decode_string", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "run", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "run.df", "type": {"name": "pl.DataFrame", "xref": {"fqname": "polars.DataFrame", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "run.result_df", "type": {"name": "pl.DataFrame", "xref": {"fqname": "polars.DataFrame", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "polars_deunicode_string.typing", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "polars_deunicode_string.typing.IntoExprColumn", "type": {"name": "TypeAlias", "xref": {"fqname": "typing_extensions.TypeAlias", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "polars